    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan before we proceed:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Add `Stepper` Compound Component\n\n### What will be created (4 changes total)\n\n**2 new files:**\n1. `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/stepper.tsx` — the component\n2. `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/stepper-demo.tsx` — the demo\n\n**2 registry edits (append only):**\n3. `ui/_registry.ts` — add `stepper` entry between `spinner` and `switch`\n4. `examples/_registry.ts` — add `stepper-demo` entry between the `spinner-*` entries and `switch-demo`\n\n---\n\n### Architecture of `stepper.tsx`\n\n**Two React contexts** (modeled after `carousel.tsx`):\n- `StepperContext` → provides `activeStep` + `orientation` to all descendants\n- `StepperItemContext` → provides `step` + computed `state` (`\"completed\" | \"active\" | \"pending\"`)\n\n| Component | Element | Key behavior |\n|-----------|---------|-------------|\n| `Stepper` | `<div>` | Root; `flex-row` or `flex-col`; `data-orientation` attr |\n| `StepperItem` | `<div>` | Computes `state`; sets `data-step` + `data-state` |\n| `StepperTrigger` | `<button>` | Shows step number by default; styled per state (solid=completed, outlined=active, muted=pending) |\n| `StepperTitle` | `<p>` | Label text |\n| `StepperDescription` | `<p>` | Muted sub-label |\n| `StepperSeparator` | `<div>` | Lives _inside_ `StepperItem`; highlights when `state === \"completed\"` |\n| `StepperContent` | `<div>` | Returns `null` unless `step === activeStep` |\n\n**Key design decision**: `StepperSeparator` is placed at the end of each `StepperItem` (except the last). This gives it access to `StepperItemContext` so it can highlight automatically when that step is completed — no extra props needed.\n\n**No external npm dependencies** — only React + `cn()`.\n\n---\n\n### Demo\n- 3 steps: Account → Profile → Complete\n- `React.useState(1)` controls active step\n- Previous/Next buttons with boundary guards\n- `StepperContent` panels swap per active step",
